I didn&#39;t have luck doing above -- probably because Heritrix does its own 
config. of the logger as soon as it comes up perhaps overwriting the 
cmdline config. (I didn&#39;t spend time figuring why).

But making a change like the below in heritrix.properties seems to do 
the trick:

Index: src/conf/heritrix.properties
===================================================================
RCS file: 
/cvsroot/archive-crawler/ArchiveOpenCrawler/src/conf/heritrix.properties,v
retrieving revision 1.63
diff -u -r1.63 heritrix.properties
--- src/conf/heritrix.properties        2 Dec 2005 02:20:31 -0000       1.63
+++ src/conf/heritrix.properties        16 Dec 2005 17:07:36 -0000
@@ -132,6 +132,8 @@

  # Leave RecoveryJournal level at INFO to see recovery progress
  org.archive.crawler.frontier.RecoveryJournal.level = INFO
+javax.management.remote.rmi.level = FINEST
+javax.management.mbeanserver.level = FINEST


And  yes, the output shows in heritrix_out.log or in your eclipse 
console screen.

Good luck,
St.Ack


